main event: A ball of fire exploded over Washington state at 0030 PST on May 30, 1952.
interesting points: The object was bright white and similar to a meteor that exploded on May 11.
The object was seen by a state policeman who said it seemed to be over Port Townsend.
The report was recorded as part of Project Blue Book, the U.S. Air Force's official study of UFOs.
The observation was classified as a 'vague' report, likely a large meteor.
The report includes 6 photographs of the event, though no photographs are present in the provided image.
sighted object: A bright white ball of fire
